TopicTitle: tiny mod suggestion - may look like a excel tab

Articles.Content:
Hello C,

First a quick replay.

I normaly use 20-30 mods and i love to reenact real missions aso., for sure in career.

Fastly i lost overview and i started to document/record my missions.This escalated totally and finaly i made this: (see below, the tab was from an early start)

This Tabs are structured in sheets

"overview sheet" where i see programms stats/finances

"Mission control" where i document every launch + some stats

"Parts" where i document lifter, which are saved as own vessels in the vab/sph (faster way to attach them to created vessels), also airplanes aso. + stats

and a few other ones.

 

But before i could start trough my savefile is corrupt cause the 1.1 update but im ready for a new career. My list of mods i will use is already finished.

Now my big question/request to modders: Is it possible to insert such tabs, connected to Money flow aso.?

I'm anoyed from shift-tabing to Excel and back ^^

I'm in the process of trying to build exactly this tool. You can check out some pictures here of the progress. I'm working on minimizing the amount of time needed to log all the specific things. This includes automated import of kerbal details, contracts etc. It's designed to be used outside the game itself but greatly reduces the amount of information you need to manually input. I'm looking for suggestions if you have any!
